	The following are the two deals that were presented at the RAC meeting last week, and should be communicated to Government Affairs:
1.
Region:  EWS/EA/East Power

Deal Name: Brooklyn Navy Yard

Originator: David Marks

Description: Acquisition of 50% interest in 286 MW CCGT in Brooklyn, NY from Edison Mission Energy.  Edison has outstanding litigation with EPC Contractor and has 	      agreed to indemnify partnership and Enron for costs associated with outcome.

